Osun State governor Gboyega Oyetola on Tuesday extended the state lockdown for another 14 days. “In order to ensure a total defeat of coronavirus in Osun, we shall extend lockdown by another 14 days,” Oyetola said in his statewide broadcast. “But to allow our people to re-stock to survive this lockdown period, the lockdown is suspended between Wednesday, 15th and Thursday, 16th April, 2020,” he added. Oyetola said the decision was imperative in view of the devastating nature of the pandemic. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .